Package com.embeddedunveiled.serial

Interface Summary
IPortMonitor Whenever an opened port has been removed, native layer will call this method of the registered listener.
ISerialComDataListener This interface represents Completion handler in our proactor design pattern.
ISerialComEventListener This interface represents Completion handler in our proactor design pattern.
 

Class Summary
SerialComCompletionDispatcher This class represents Proactor in our IO design pattern.
SerialComDataEvent This class encapsulate data received from serial port.
SerialComErrorMapper This class gives consistent error in java layer mapping OS specific error numbers.
SerialComJNINativeInterface This class load native library and is an interface between java and native modules.
SerialComLineEvent This class encapsulate events that happens on serial port control lines.
SerialComLooper This class runs in as a different thread context and keep looping over event queue, delivering events to the intended registered listener (event handler) one by one.
SerialComManager This class is the entry point to this library.
SerialComPortHandleInfo This class contain information about The association that exist among port name, its corresponding handle, looper, data and event listener.
SerialComPortsList This class arranges serial port names found in the system in alphanumeric order.
 

Enum Summary
SerialComManager.BAUDRATE Pre-defined constants for baud rate values.
SerialComManager.DATABITS Pre-defined constants for number of data bits in a serial frame.
SerialComManager.ENDIAN Pre-defined constants for defining endianness of data to be sent over serial port.
SerialComManager.FLOWCONTROL Pre-defined constants for controlling data flow between DTE and DCE.
SerialComManager.NUMOFBYTES Pre-defined constants for defining number of bytes given data can be represented in.
SerialComManager.PARITY Pre-defined constants for enabling type of parity in a serial frame.
SerialComManager.STOPBITS Pre-defined constants for number of stop bits in a serial frame.
